  schema:name "Rubber-Hose Realism" ;
  schema:description "A moral-physics regime in which bodies are elastic, harm is reversible, and the world resets between scenes — first stabilized in 1920s American animation and now redeployed across commercial entertainment, soft power, and overt psychological operations." ;
